up B,E)$ that has an easily computable balanced vertex\nseparator for every subgraph $G'(V',E')$ of size $|V'|^{\\delta}$, for\n$\\delta\\in [1/2,1)$, we can apply our algorithm to compute a maximum matching\nin $\\tilde{\\mathcal{O}}(mn^{\\frac{\\delta}{1+\\delta}})$ time improving upon the\n$\\mathcal{O}(m\\sqrt{n})$ time taken by the HK-Algorithm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Mar 2019 16:27:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-26"}
