warf galaxies and have survived for several hundred million years.\nTherefore our study shows that extended tidal dwarf galaxies and compact\nclusters may be formed simultaneously. In the specific case observed here, the\nyoung star clusters are not massive enough to survive for a Hubble time.\nHowever one may speculate that similar objects at higher redshift, with higher\nstar formation rate, might form some of the long lived globular clusters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Mar 2019 10:56:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Jun 2019 13:35:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-14"}
